This paper is primarily focused on the problem of malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also makes use of machine learning techniques to aggregate and analyze data from multiple sources, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of statistical analysis and neighborhood-level features, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
